Title: Closed-Loop Shipping Lanes: Turning Freight Transport into Self-Sustaining Environmental Assets
Sections:
	•	Abstract: Modular container ecosystems capturing CO₂, producing algae, generating energy en route.
	•	Problem Statement: Shipping is a massive source of emissions and pollution.
	•	Proposed Solution: Retrofit shipping containers for modular, multi-purpose environmental services.
	•	Technical Design: Containerized energy & waste systems, algae cultivation, CO₂ capture.
	•	Deployment & Testing: Pilot container integration on freight routes.
	•	Use Cases: Carbon capture, renewable energy generation, sustainable shipping.
	•	Impact & Scalability: Global shipping decarbonization, modular and scalable adoption.
	•	Future Research & Partnerships: Logistics companies, maritime agencies, environmental NGOs.
